article.headline: Wecker notches 26th career double-double
article.linkText: No. 13 K-State rolls over winless Sacramento State
article.story:
MANHATTAN, Kan. (AP) -- Kendra Wecker had 20 points and 16
rebounds for her 26th career double-double, and No. 13 Kansas State
beat winless Sacramento State 94-31 Friday night in the first round
of the Commerce Bank Wildcat Classic.

Laurie Koehn, six-of-eight from 3-point range, also had 20.

Nicole Ohlde and Brie Madden added 12 points apiece for Kansas
State (4-2). The Wildcats won for the 11th straight time in their
own tournament and got their 22nd consecutive regular-season home
victory.

Tyeisha Brown led Sacramento State (0-6) with 11 points.

The Hornets had nine turnovers in the first eight minutes as the
Wildcats pulled away quickly.

Ohlde hit a layup and two free throws to ignite a 17-2 run with
15:48 to go in the first half for a 28-8 lead. Ohlde was perfect in
the spurt, making two baskets and six free throws.

Kansas State led 52-22 at the break, then scored 13 straight
points to start the second half.

The Wildcats will play Saint Louis on Saturday for the
tournament title.
